This page demonstrates how to implement consistent button styling across your projects using OEDA brand colors and design patterns.


Use primary buttons for the main action on a page or section.



Primary Action


Disabled Primary




&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Primary Action&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" disabled&gt;Disabled Primary&lt;/button&gt;



/*-- scss:rules --*/

.btn-primary {
  background-color: var(--bs-primary);
  border-color: var(--bs-primary);
  color: white;
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  background-color: var(--bs-secondary);
  border-color: var(--bs-secondary);
}

.btn-primary:disabled {
  opacity: 0.6;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}




Use secondary buttons for supporting actions or when you need multiple buttons in close proximity.



Secondary Action


Outlined Button




&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary"&gt;Secondary Action&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary"&gt;Outlined Button&lt;/button&gt;




